@0    = ~This is a laboratory bench, but you are too far away to make use of it.~
@1    = ~You rummage through the documents for information about the items in your pack. The blue powder seems to be an adhesive that, if laid upon a surface, will form a durable coating. You see figures that show how to dredge a rough surface to obtain an even result. However, you have nothing that you want to use it on.~
@2    = ~You browse the documents for information about the items in your pack. The blue powder seems to be an adhesive that, if laid upon a surface, will form a durable coating. You see figures that show how to dredge a rough surface to obtain an even result. However, you have nothing that you want to use it on. This could make the invisible rune visible, but why would you do that?~
@3    = ~Now, since you have all the necessary articles together and know what you want to make with them, you can use the lab bench to make the invisible rune visible with the blue powder.~
@4    = ~You dust the invisible rune with the binding powder and receive a visible magic rune, which you stow away in your luggage.~
@5    = ~The lab bench served its purpose. There is no further use for it.~
@6    = ~You examine the laboratory bench. Various instruction books for the production of magic articles lie on it, but you would not know what to do with them.~
